What is GUser and How to use it

GUser is a derived c++ class from GAcq. GUser is available to user wanting to introduce specific C++ code to analyse Ganil data.

GUser is composed of 6 empty methods ready to be fill by user.

InitUser() is called  by SetUserMode()
InitUserRun()is called by DoRun  
User() is called for each new event
EndUserRun() is call either DoRun is finished either on a Stop 
EndUser() is called by EndUser

and  InitTTreeUser() is used to define branch in case TTree output is validated

To compile GUser and load it
-either you do a "make" and do  a "gROOT->ProcessLine(".L ./GUser_C.so");" in GRU to load  it
-either do in GRU
  "gROOT->ProcessLine(".include /home/acqexp/GRU/GRUcurrent/include");


